value.value: Human HIVEP1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 6p24.1 and is approximately 157 kb in length. This allele, which encodes zinc finger protein 40, is involved in the modulation of viral and cellular gene expression.
A type of pharmaceutical dose form that may be liquid, semi-solid or solid, to be added to a large volume of diluent, such as in a bath.

label.value: Anticoagulant and Preservative Solution for Blood Dosage Form

value.value: Sterile aqueous liquid preparation intended to be mixed with extracorporeal blood to preserve the blood and prevent coagulation.
The technique of administration of a pharmaceutical product by placing or spreading it onto the affected area.
Device for delivery of a solid dose into the throat of the animal.
A unit of presentation used to represent the quantity of product that is found in a single barrel container.
A pharmaceutical dose form that is added to a bath.
The technique of administration of a pharmaceutical product by immersing all or part of the affected area in the product, sometimes for an extended period of time.
Administration of a veterinary medicinal product by dipping the beak of birds into an aqueous solution of the medicinal product.
Pharmaceutical impregnated strips that deliver the active substance(s) when lit. This is used to treat bee hives and nests.
Pharmaceutical impregnated sticks that deliver the active substance(s) when lit. This is used to treat bee hives and nests.

label.value: Beehive Dispersion in Sachet Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of a bee-hive dispersion presented in a sachet.
Semi-solid multidose preparation intended for veterinary use, consisting of a gel from which the active substance(s) are released by vaporization or physical contact over an extended period of time.

Liquid preparation intended for in-hive use, consisting of a solution from which the active substance(s) are released by vaporization or physical contact usually over an extended period of time. The precise method of administration of the solution is described in the product information.

Solid preparation for veterinary use consisting of a matrix impregnated with active substance(s) that are released by vaporization or physical contact over an extended period of time. Any specific requirements for the placing of the bee-hive strip are described in the product information.
Sterile liquid preparation intended for irrigation of the urinary bladder.
Administration device fitted with a fine brush used for the application of liquid pharmaceutical forms.
A closure with a brush device.
The technique of administration of a pharmaceutical product by lighting it in order to evolve smoke that is taken in by the subject.
A unit of presentation used to represent the quantity of product that is found in a single discrete entity where the pharmaceutical dose form is a type of cachet.
Solid discoid preparation consisting of a wafer enclosing a unit dose intended for oral use.

label.value: Hard Capsule plus Tablet Dosage Form

value.value: Combination package consisting of a hard capsule and a tablet.

label.value: Soft Capsule plus Tablet Dosage Form

value.value: Combination package consisting of a soft capsule and a tablet.
A soft tablet that must be chewed to release the active and/or inert ingredient(s).
An uncoated tablet intended either to be chewed before being swallowed, or to be dispersed in the specified liquid before being swallowed.
The technique of administration of a pharmaceutical product by crushing or grinding it with the teeth; after chewing, some products are intended to be swallowed, some are intended to be spat out.
A closure which is difficult for young children to open but which is not difficult for adults to open properly.

label.value: Coated Granules in Sachet Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of coated granules presented in a sachet.
Liquid preparation usually containing pyroxylin in a mixture of ether and ethanol. When applied to the skin, the preparation forms a flexible film on the site of application.

Solid single-dose preparation intended to be sucked to obtain a local or systemic effect. It is prepared by compression and is often rhomboid in shape. Compressed lozenges usually contain flavoring and sweetening agents. They dissolve or disintegrate slowly when sucked.

label.value: Concentrate and Solvent for Concentrate for Oral Spray, Suspension Dosage Form

value.value: A concentrate and a solvent intended for the preparation of a concentrate for oral spray, suspension by diluting the concentrate with the solvent; the resulting concentrate for oral spray, suspension must subsequently be diluted again before administration as an oral spray, suspension.

label.value: Concentrate and Solvent for Concentrate for Solution for Infusion Dosage Form

value.value: Sterile concentrate and sterile solvent intended for the preparation of a concentrate for solution for infusion by diluting the concentrate with the solvent; the resulting concentrate for solution for infusion must subsequently be diluted again before administration as a solution for infusion.

label.value: Concentrate and Solvent for Cutaneous Solution Dosage Form

value.value: Concentrate and solvent intended for the preparation of a cutaneous solution by diluting the concentrate with the solvent.

label.value: Concentrate and Solvent for Solution for Infusion Dosage Form

value.value: Sterile concentrate and sterile solvent intended for the preparation of a solution for infusion by diluting the concentrate with the solvent.

label.value: Concentrate and Solvent for Solution for Injection Dosage Form

value.value: Sterile concentrate and sterile solvent intended for the preparation of a solution for injection by diluting the concentrate with the solvent.

label.value: Concentrate and Solvent for Solution for Injection/Infusion Dosage Form

value.value: Sterile concentrate and sterile solvent intended for the preparation of a solution for injection/infusion by diluting the concentrate with the solvent.

label.value: Concentrate and Solvent for Suspension for Injection Dosage Form

value.value: Sterile concentrate and sterile solvent intended for the preparation of a suspension for injection by diluting the concentrate with the solvent.

label.value: Concentrate for Concentrate for Oral Spray, Suspension Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid preparation for veterinary use intended to be diluted in the specified liquid to obtain a concentrate for oral spray, suspension, which in turn is intended to be diluted in the specified liquid to obtain an oral spray, suspension.

label.value: Concentrate for Concentrate for Solution for Infusion Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile preparation intended to be diluted in the specified liquid to obtain a concentrate for solution for infusion, which in turn is intended to be diluted in the specified liquid to obtain a solution for infusion.

label.value: Concentrate for Cutaneous Solution Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid preparation intended to be diluted in the specified liquid to obtain a cutaneous solution.

label.value: Concentrate for Cutaneous Spray, Emulsion Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid preparation intended to be diluted in the specified liquid to obtain a cutaneous spray emulsion.

label.value: Concentrate for Dip Emulsion Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid preparation intended to be diluted in the specified liquid to obtain a dip emulsion.

label.value: Concentrate for Dip Solution Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid preparation intended to be diluted in the specified liquid to obtain a dip solution.

label.value: Concentrate for Dip Suspension Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid preparation intended to be diluted in the specified liquid to obtain a dip suspension.

label.value: Concentrate for Dispersion for Infusion Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile preparation intended to be diluted in the specified liquid to obtain a dispersion for infusion.
